    <h1>Every Weekend Another Film Pairing</h1>
     <!-- Link to my CSS stylesheet -->
    <link rel="CSS Style Sheet" href="CSS Style Sheet">
    <p>
<img src="https://images.everydayhealth.com/images/emotional-health/why-you-like-rewatching-tv-shows-1440x810.jpg?sfvrsn=f78ed51a_5" alt="Two women one with locs, and the other with braids are watching Friends sitting on a couch. On the tv screen in front of them we can see Rachel, and Monica are on screen.">
  <p>
        Ever since I was a kid I have always loved watching as many movies as I can! 
        Below you'll find a list of films I watched last weekend lest you should chicken out 
        on the double feature for fear that there might be too few hours in a day. 
        It may shock you these pairings. However for the time being I am choosing to extrapolate 
        from it only a childish playfulness combined with the often unbelievably, and occasionally
        too perfect summation that is screenwriting. Positing that I am somehow simply drawn 
        to juxtapositions for reasons perhaps better answered to by my psychoanalyst. This is for you, 
        however! Indulge with me. Barely lift your head off of the sofa, or your body. 
    </p>
    
    <ul>
        <li>Boogie Nights</li>
        <li>Zootopia</li>
        <li>American Psycho</li>
        <li>A Little Princess</li>
    </ul>

    <p></p>

